title: Fragment of Amulet of Tuamutef [or Anubis]
description: pressed into a mold. Tuamutef - Mummiform figure with the head of a jackal (or dog?). One of the four sons of Horus. Protected the stomach of the dead, which was embalmed in the third canopic jar.-Alan W. Shorter,"The Egyptian Gods", p.143.  Anubis - Man with the head of a jackal.
